# Sri.OS Portfolio — Phase 3 Suggestions

Congrats on shipping Phase 2! Here's a prioritized breakdown of what to tackle next, organized by **impact vs. effort**.

---

## 🔴 High Impact (Do These First)

### 1. Fix the Broken Project Image: `data_labeler_showcase.png`
- [portfolio.json](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/lib/portfolio.json) references `/data_labeler_showcase.png` for the "Autonomous Data Labeler" project, but that file does **not** exist in `/public/`.
- The project card will show a broken image on the live site.
- **Fix**: Add the image to `/public/`, or update the `image` field to an existing file.

### 2. Fix the Email Link Format in [portfolio.json](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/lib/portfolio.json)
- `"email": "[sriramamurthychellu@gmail.com]"` — brackets are included in the raw string.
- This will produce a broken `mailto:` link (`mailto:[sriramamurthy...]` instead of `mailto:sriramamurthy...`).
- **Fix**: Remove the brackets: `"email": "sriramamurthychellu@gmail.com"`.

### 3. Image Optimization — Large Uncompressed Photos
- Several photos in `/public/Photography/` & root are **multi-megabyte JPGs** (e.g., [Sri.png](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/public/Sri.png) = 1.7 MB, `GenAI Bioinfo.png` = 6.6 MB).
- These will significantly hurt LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) scores and mobile load times.
- **Fix**: Run `next/image` with `quality={80}` and proper `sizes` props on all photo pages. For the `/public/Photography/` folder, consider running them through `sharp` or `squoosh` to get them under 300 KB each.

### 4. Add `resumé` Link / Download Button
- You have GitHub, LinkedIn, and Email in the hero, but **no resume/CV link**.
- This is the #1 thing recruiters look for — it needs to be immediately accessible.
- **Fix**: Add a `FileText` (Lucide) icon button next to the social icons in the Hero, linking to a PDF in `/public/`.

---

## 🟡 Medium Impact (Great Polish)

### 5. Now-Playing API: Cache the Spotify Response
- [route.ts](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/app/api/now-playing/route.ts) calls `getNowPlaying()` on every request.
- [SpotifyNowPlaying.tsx](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/components/SpotifyNowPlaying.tsx) polls every **30 seconds** on the client.
- If many visitors are online simultaneously, this burns Spotify API quota fast.
- **Fix**: Add a simple in-memory cache with a 25s TTL in [app/api/now-playing/route.ts](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/app/api/now-playing/route.ts):
  ```ts
  // Cache result for 25s to avoid hammering the Spotify API
  let cache: { data: object; ts: number } | null = null;
  if (cache && Date.now() - cache.ts < 25_000) return NextResponse.json(cache.data);
  ```

### 6. Add `og:image` / Open Graph Metadata
- The sitemetadata in [app/layout.tsx](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/app/layout.tsx) is likely minimal. When you share your portfolio on LinkedIn or Twitter, there's no rich preview card.
- **Fix**: Add to [layout.tsx](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/app/layout.tsx):
  ```ts
  openGraph: {
    title: 'Srirama Murthy Chellu — AI/ML Engineer',
    description: '...',
    images: [{ url: '/Sri.png', width: 1200, height: 630 }],
  },
  twitter: { card: 'summary_large_image', ... }
  ```

### 7. Keyboard Accessibility for the AI Chat
- The chat input relies on `onFocus` to open and `click` to close, but there's no `Escape` key handler to close the panel.
- **Fix**: Add a `keydown` listener: `if (e.key === 'Escape') handleClose();`
- Also add `aria-live="polite"` on the messages container so screen readers announce new messages.

### 8. Photography Page: Add Category Filter
- The `/photography` page has 30+ photos. Looking at the data, there are rich categories: `Aerial`, `Event`, `Heritage`, `Landscape`, `Astro`, `Urban`, etc.
- A filter bar (even just a row of pill buttons) would make the gallery much more browsable.
- This would also be consistent with the Skills page's approach to organizing content.

### 9. Duplicate Photo Titles in [portfolio.json](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/lib/portfolio.json)
- There are **3 entries all titled `"Charminar"`** (ids 7, 8, 9) and all from Hyderabad. If they're distinct shots, give them unique titles: `Charminar — Dusk`, `Charminar — Close`, etc.
- Similarly, the location `"Hyderabad"` is sometimes spelled `"Hyderbad"` (typo in IDs 22, 23, 27, 29).

### 10. Work Experience: Location Inconsistency
- [portfolio.json](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/lib/portfolio.json) says `"location": "San Francisco, CA"` in personal info, but [page.tsx](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/app/page.tsx) hero text says "building in Los Angeles, California."
- **Fix**: Update personal.location to `"Los Angeles, CA"` to match the hero copy.

---

## 🟢 Nice-to-Have (Phase 3 Features)

### 11. Add a `Contact` Section / Page
- Currently the only way to reach you is email (which has the broken bracket issue noted above).
- A simple contact form with Name, Email, and Message would feel more complete and professional.
- Could be a `/contact` route or a bottom-of-page section on the home layout.

### 12. Typing Indicator in AI Chat is Missing a "Max Retries" State
- In [PortfolioAssistant.tsx](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/components/PortfolioAssistant.tsx), if the API call fails, you show a red error string.
- But if the fetch itself hangs (e.g., timeout), there's no timeout handling — the loading dots spin forever.
- **Fix**: Add an `AbortController` with a 15s timeout to the [handleSend](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/components/PortfolioAssistant.tsx#417-442) fetch call.
  ```ts
  const controller = new AbortController();
  const timeout = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 15_000);
  const res = await fetch('/api/chat', { signal: controller.signal, ... });
  clearTimeout(timeout);
  ```

### 13. Neural Breaker Game: Add a High Score Persistence
- The game currently resets the high score on page reload. Since you already have the Spotify widget data persisted, a simple `localStorage` save for the high score would be a nice touch:
  ```ts
  const [hiScore, setHiScore] = useState(() => Number(localStorage.getItem('nb-hi') ?? 0));
  ```

### 14. Add a `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt`
- For SEO, these are essential for Google to properly index your portfolio.
- With Next.js 13+ App Router, you can add:
  - `app/sitemap.ts` — returns your page URLs
  - `app/robots.ts` — sets crawl rules
- This is a 10-minute win for discoverability.

### 15. `TintSwitcher` — Persist Tint Across Page Navigations
- When the user switches tint to "Lavender" then navigates to `/skills`, the tint resets to default if the switcher state isn't persisted.
- **Fix**: Store selected tint in `localStorage` and restore it on mount in the `TintSwitcher` component.

### 16. Hero Section — Resume the Polaroid Animation on Mobile
- On mobile, the hero polaroid photo is hidden (the mobile layout is different). But the [MobileHomeLayout.tsx](file:///e:/VSC/Portfolio/sri-os/components/MobileHomeLayout.tsx) likely has its own structure.
- Consider showing a compact version of the polaroid or a circular avatar on mobile to maintain the personal touch.

